3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EConstipation%20is%20common%2C%20but%20you%20can%20introduce%20things%20to%20your%20routine%20to%20relieve%20symptoms.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDoing%20abdominal%20massage%20after%20a%20meal%20and%20getting%20more%20movement%20into%20your%20day%20can%20help.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20an%20occupational%20therapist%20specializing%20in%20pelvic%20health%2C%20I%20recommend%20these%20tips.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHave%20you%20ever%20noticed%20that%20if%20you%20drink%20coffee%20daily%2C%20it's%20almost%20as%20if%20just%20the%20smell%20of%20coffee%20beans%20can%20get%20your%20intestines%20moving%3F%20Or%20have%20you%20found%20yourself%20going%20straight%20for%20the%20restroom%20when%20you%20walk%20into%20work%3F%20It's%20because%20your%20bowels%20love%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20are%20also%20many%20things%20that%20can%20interfere%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fchronic-constipation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproper%20bowel%20function%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Medication%2C%20stress%2C%20travel%2C%20hormones%2C%20nutrition%2C%20muscle%20tension%2C%20and%20even%20your%20positioning%20on%20the%20toilet%20all%20play%20a%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.lww.com%2Fajg%2Fabstract%2F2004%2F04000%2Fepidemiology_of_constipation_in_north_america__a.30.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E63%20million%20Americans%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20experience%20constipation%2C%20but%20understanding%20the%20principles%20of%20healthy%20digestion%20and%20habit%20building%20can%20help%20reduce%20symptoms.%20By%20incorporating%20simple%2C%20everyday%20routines%20that%20naturally%20stimulate%20digestive%20movement%2C%20we%20can%20train%20our%20bowels%20to%20function%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20occupational%20therapist%20who%20specializes%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-to-poop-constipation-pelvic-floor-health-fiber-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epelvic%20health%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20frequently%20see%20patients%20with%20constipation%20and%20help%20them%20relieve%20their%20symptoms%20by%20getting%20their%20bowels%20into%20a%20routine.%20Here%20are%20some%20simple%20remedies%20to%20help%20you%20get%20your%20own%20symptoms%20under%20control%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDrink%20a%20warm%20beverage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStarting%20the%20morning%20%E2%80%94%20or%20whatever%20time%20you%20aim%20to%20establish%20a%20bowel%20routine%20%E2%80%94%20off%20with%20hot%20tea%2C%20coffee%2C%20or%20water%20can%20do%20wonders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20jobs%20of%20the%20small%20intestine%20is%20to%20pull%20out%20most%20of%20the%20water%20consumed%20via%20food%20and%20drinks.%20If%20you're%20dehydrated%2C%20waste%20can%20harden%20and%20become%20stuck.%20Adding%20more%20water%20of%20any%20temperature%20to%20the%20digestive%20tract%20helps%20keep%20stools%20soft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrinking%20hot%20beverages%20can%20break%20down%20food%20faster%20than%20cold%20or%20room-temperature%20water%2C%20as%20the%20heat%20widens%20blood%20vessels%2C%20increases%20blood%20flow%2C%20and%20speeds%20up%20digestive%20motility.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F19308311%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecouple%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20small%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F27684632%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudies%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20found%20warm%20beverages%20may%20positively%20affect%20intestinal%20movements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recommend%20aiming%20to%20drink%201%20ounce%20of%20water%20(of%20any%20temperature)%20for%20every%202%20pounds%20of%20your%20body%20weight%20each%20day.%20It%20may%20also%20be%20helpful%20to%20include%20a%20hot%20beverage%20as%20part%20of%20your%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETry%20an%20abdominal%20massage%20after%20eating%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC10366436%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAbdominal%20massage%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20increase%20the%20frequency%20of%20evacuation%20and%20reduce%20symptoms%20of%20difficult%20defecation.%20Many%20pelvic-health%20professionals%20refer%20to%20it%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BI%20Love%20U%26quot%3B%20belly%20massage%20because%20you%20trace%20the%20letters%20I%2C%20L%2C%20and%20U%20on%20your%20belly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20easy%20and%20takes%20only%20about%205%20to%2010%20minutes.%20Aim%20to%20do%20this%20massage%2030%20to%2060%20minutes%20after%20a%20meal.%20The%20steps%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ELie%20down%20on%20your%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20your%20left%20side%2C%20just%20under%20your%20rib%20cage%2C%20apply%20gentle%20pressure%20as%20you%20move%20your%20hand%20in%20a%20straight%20line%20(like%20the%20letter%20I)%20down%20the%20top%20of%20the%20left%20hip%20bone.%20Repeat%2010%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20from%20right%20to%20left%2C%20run%20your%20hand%20in%20a%20straight%20line%20across%20the%20top%20of%20your%20belly%20just%20beneath%20the%20rib%20cage%2C%20applying%20gentle%20pressure.%20Continue%20applying%20pressure%2C%20and%20run%20your%20hand%20along%20the%20same%20line%20down%20your%20left%20hip%20bone%20as%20you%20just%20did%20in%20the%20previous%20step%20to%20create%20an%20inverted%20L%20shape.%20Again%2C%20repeat%2010%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20gently%20apply%20pressure%20from%20the%20hip%20bone%20on%20the%20right%20side%20and%20move%20up%20to%20your%20rib%20cage%2C%20across%20your%20belly%2C%20then%20over%20and%20down%20your%20left%20hip%20bone%20to%20create%20an%20inverted%20U.%20Repeat%2010%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIntroduce%20movement%20into%20your%20day%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMovement%20brings%20blood%20flow%20to%20the%20muscles%20in%20our%20digestive%20system%2C%20which%20then%20massages%20our%20food%20down%20the%20digestive%20tract.%20Break%20up%20your%20day%20with%20several%2010-minute%20walks%2C%20or%20find%20aerobic%20exercises%20you%20like%20to%20do%20and%20add%20them%20to%20your%20routine%2C%20such%20as%20jogging%2C%20swimming%2C%20or%20biking.%20As%20long%20as%20there's%20consistency%2C%20these%20are%20all%20great%20ways%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fhow-often-should-you-poop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejump-start%20your%20digestive%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStretches%20or%20yoga%20positions%20such%20as%20twists%2C%20side%20bends%2C%20and%20forward%20folds%20are%20also%20helpful%2C%20as%20they%20can%20put%20pressure%20on%20the%20abdomen%2C%20which%20encourages%20circulation%20and%20reduces%20bloating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGo%20for%20solid%20foods%20before%20a%20breakfast%20smoothie%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20packed%20with%20fruits%20and%20fiber%2C%20shakes%20and%20smoothies%20may%20feel%20like%20a%20healthy%20option%2C%20but%20they%20can%20contribute%20to%20digestive%20problems%20for%20a%20few%20reasons.%20Additives%20and%20artificial%20sweeteners%20can%20cause%20constipation%2C%20bloating%2C%20and%20gas.%20Everyone's%20gut%20has%20its%20own%20delicate%20balance%2C%20so%20what%20may%20be%20helpful%20for%20one%20person%20can%20cause%20issues%20for%20someone%20else.%20If%20you%20tend%20to%20start%20your%20day%20with%20a%20protein%20shake%20or%20smoothie%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fnatural-laxatives-home-remedies-constipation-relief-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexperience%20constipation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20try%20swapping%20it%20out%20for%20a%20breakfast%20of%20solid%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20physical%20act%20of%20chewing%20increases%20saliva%20production%2C%20which%20signals%20the%20gut%20to%20metabolize%20and%20digest.%20Chewing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20chewing%20your%20food%20well%20%E2%80%94%20supports%20digestion.%20My%20favorite%20solid%20breakfast%20go-tos%20are%20oatmeal%20with%20berries%2C%20yogurt%20and%20fruit%20(such%20as%20kiwi%2C%20raspberries%2C%20apples%2C%20and%20pears)%20with%20chia%20seeds%20or%20flaxseeds%2C%20and%20whole-grain%20toast%20with%20avocado.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHabits%20always%20take%20a%20bit%20of%20time%20to%20establish%2C%20but%20with%20consistency%2C%20you%20may%20surprise%20yourself%20with%20how%20happy%20your%20gut%20and%20bowels%20are%20with%20these%20simple%20daily%20routines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconstipation-remedies-habits-symptoms-routine-tips-pelvic-health-expert-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703883566000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658f0eb1ab6f2ebb11f7cf12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconstipation-remedies-habits-symptoms-routine-tips-pelvic-health-expert-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Constipation%20is%20common%2C%20but%20symptoms%20can%20be%20relieved%20by%20creating%20a%20routine.%20Habits%20like%20abdominal%20massage%20and%20motion%20can%20help%20with%20bowel%20movements.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Dana%20Solomon)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A87%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconstipation-remedies-habits-symptoms-routine-tips-pelvic-health-expert-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lew%20Rothman%2C%20Veteran%20Entertainment%20Executive%2C%20Dies%20at%2063%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703883423000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fupload