scow%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F29184807%2FGCW4z6zWEAAr0qe.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandigarh%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20status%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20prime%20materiel%20provider%20for%20over%20six%20decades%20is%20steadily%20declining%2C%20as%20subtly%20evidenced%20during%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%E2%80%99s%20recently%20concluded%20Moscow%20visit%2C%20aimed%20at%20boosting%20bilateral%20strategic%2C%20defence%2C%20diplomatic%20and%20political%20ties%2C%20between%20hoary%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELittle%20other%20than%20shibboleths%20and%20routine%20effusive%20hyperbole%20emerged%20officially%20after%20Jaishankar%E2%80%99s%20interactions%20with%20various%20Russian%20leaders%2C%20including%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20during%20his%20five-day%20trip%2C%20particularly%20with%20regard%20to%20military%20commerce%20between%20the%20two%20sides.%20Significantly%2C%20there%20was%20no%20public%20mention%2C%20or%20even%20hint%2C%20of%20revised%20schedules%20in%20delivering%20assorted%20%C2%A0outstanding%20Russian%20platforms%20to%20India%2C%20alongside%20badly-needed%20spares%20and%20associated%20kit%20for%20in-service%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENor%20was%20there%20any%20indication%20of%20the%20two%20sides%20having%20resolved%20the%20knotty%20problem%20of%20India%20paying%20Russia%20for%20military%20gear%2C%20which%20has%20been%20bedevilling%20both%20sides%20for%2012-14%20months%2C%20after%20US-led%20sanctions%20were%20imposed%20on%20Russia%20for%20invading%20Ukraine%2C%20in%20February%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20after%20meeting%20Jaishankar%2C%20his%20Russian%20counterpart%20Sergei%20Lavrov%20evasively%20declared%20that%20both%20sides%20had%20%E2%80%98discussed%E2%80%99%20the%20prospects%20of%20military%20and%20technical%20cooperation%2C%20including%20the%20joint%20production%20of%20modern%20weaponry%E2%80%99%20as%20part%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Make%20in%20India%E2%80%99%20initiative%2C%20but%20declined%20to%20elaborate%20further%20on%20its%20contours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETellingly%2C%20Lavrov%20also%20stated%20that%20Russia%20was%20%E2%80%98respectful%E2%80%99%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20aspiration%20to%20%E2%80%98diversify%E2%80%99%20its%20military%20equipment%20and%20related%20technical%20links%2C%20openly%20conceding%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20acceptance%20of%20the%20reality%20of%20its%20foremost%20and%20long-standing%20materiel%20customer%20seeking%20alternate%20suppliers.%20Jaishankar%2C%20for%20his%20part%2C%20too%20did%20not%20elaborate%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20defence%20partnership%20with%20Russia%2C%20stressing%20instead%20that%20bilateral%20trade%20between%20the%20two%20states%20was%20an%20at%20time%20high%20of%20%2450%20billion%20boosted%2C%20no%20doubt%2C%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20bulk%20oil%20imports%20following%20sanctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%C2%A0quick%C2%A0evaluation%C2%A0of%20the%20prevailing%20state%20of%20India-Russia%20defence%20ties%20is%C2%A0revealing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EState%20of%20affairs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20at%20present%20awaits%20delivery%20of%20three%20of%20five%20Almaz-Antey%20S-400%20Triumf%20self-propelled%20surface-to-air%20(SAM)%20missile%20systems%2C%20four%20Admiral%20Grigorovich%20Project%201135.6M%20frigates-%20two%20of%20which%20are%20to%20be%20built%20by%20Goa%20Shipyard%20Limited%20under%20a%20transfer%20of%20technology%20from%20Russia-%20and%20the%20possible%20leasing%20of%20one%20more%20Project%20971%20%E2%80%98Akula%E2%80%99%20(Schuka-B)-class%20nuclear%20powered%20submarine%20(SSN)%20for%20around%20%243%20billion%2C%20that%20was%20scheduled%20for%20delivery%20to%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20(IN)%20by%202025.%C2%A0%20This%20latter%20charter%2C%20however%2C%20remains%20chancy%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20local%20construction%20problems%20and%20sanctions-related%20complications%20and%2C%20according%20to%20industry%20officials%2C%20could%20be%20scrapped-%20if%20it%20had%20not%20been%20already-despite%20considerable%20advance%20payments%20for%20the%202019%20contract%20having%20reportedly%20been%20effected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupplying%20India%E2%80%99s%20military%2070%2C000-80%2C000%20Kalashnikov%20AK-203%207.62x39mm%20assault%20rifles%2C%20as%20part%20of%20the%20December%202021%20tender%20to%20locally%20licence%20build%20601%2C427%20of%20them%20at%20a%20facility%20in%20Korwa%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20near%20Amethi%2C%20too%20remained%20a%20work%20in%20progress.%20This%20latter%C2%A0deferral%C2%A0had%20resulted%20in%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20(MoD)%20recently%20approving%20the%20import%20of%2073%2C000%20additional%20Sig%20Sauer%20SIG716%20%E2%80%98Patrol%E2%80%99%20rifles%20from%20the%20US%20for%20Rs%20840%20crores%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20the%20Indian%20Army%20(IA).%20The%20IA%20Chief%20of%20Staff%2C%20General%20Manoj%20Pande%2C%20had%20confidently%20declared%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20his%20force%20would%20begin%20receiving%20the%20Ak-203%E2%80%99s%20by%20March%2C%20which%20obviously%20had%20not%20fructified.%20Additionally%2C%20India%20also%20awaited%20varied%20Russian%20missiles%20like%20man-portable%20Very%20Short%20Range%20Defence%20Systems%20(VSHORADS)%20and%20assorted%20other%20ammunition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Frussia-ak203-kalashnikov-ukraine-sanction%5C%22%3ERussian%20Rifle%20Delays%20Raise%20Concerns%20Over%20Deliveries%20from%20Moscow%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20exacerbating%20India%E2%80%99s%20woes%20with%20regard%20to%20military%20equipment%20purchases%20from%20Russia%2C%20was%20the%20pertinent%20issue%20of%20Delhi%20owing%C2%A0%243-4%20billion%20to%20Moscow%20as%20recurring%20payment%20for%20platforms%2C%20spares%20and%20related%20apparatus%2C%20all%20of%20which%20%C2%A0had%20accumulated%20over%20the%20several%20past%20months.%20In%20turn%2C%20this%20unsettled%20amount%20had%20resulted%20in%20Moscow%20%E2%80%98pausing%E2%80%99%20all%20further%20credit%20to%20Delhi%20for%20its%20defence%20buys.%20Furthermore%2C%20Indian%20currency%2C%20routed%20via%20%E2%80%98vostro%E2%80%99%20accounts%20through%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Sherbank%20and%20VTB%20Bank%20respectively%2C%20for%20payments%20undertaken%20under%20the%20mutually%20agreed%20rupee-rouble%20protocol%20had%2C%20to%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20financial%20chagrin%2C%20simply%20piled%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20due%20to%20Indian%20banks%C2%A0continued%20wariness%20over%20exploring%20other%20forms%20of%20payments%20to%20Russia%2C%20via%20other%20currencies%2C%20as%20suggested%20by%20Moscow%2C%20for%20fear%20of%20inviting%20secondary%20sanctions%20from%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies.%20On%20several%20previous%20occasions%C2%A0Lavrov%20had%20reiterated%20that%20Moscow%20faced%20the%20problem%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98rupee%20surfeit%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20was%20simply%20%E2%80%98unusable%2C%20as%20it%20was%20not%20a%20globally%20tradeable%20currency.%20The%20Russian%20foreign%20minister%20had%20also%20rejected%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20offer%20of%20Russia%C2%A0utilising%20the%20rupees%20from%20its%20weapon-and%20oil-%20sales%20to%20invest%20in%20Indian%20debt%20and%20capital%20markets%2C%20leaving%20the%20problem%20seemingly%20unresolved%20during%20Jaishankar%E2%80%99s%20recent%20visit%2C%20according%20to%20official%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStated%20inability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20defence%20industrial%20complex%20had%20recently%20expressed%20its%20inability%20to%20continue%20delivering%20materiel%20to%20its%20many%20clients%2C%20including%20India%2C%20as%20it%20needed%20to%20prioritise%20%E2%80%98manufacturing%20and%20supplying%20products%20to%20the%20Russian%20Army%E2%80%99.%20In%20a%20press%20statement%20in%20October%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20joint%20stock%20arms%20export%20company%20Rosonboronexport%20had%20admitted%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98pressing%20challenges%20faced%20by%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20defence%20industry%20and%20the%20system%20of%20military-technical%20co-operation%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccordingly%2C%20it%20offered%20its%20potential%20foreign%20partners%20%E2%80%98new%20formats%20of%20co-operation%20within%20the%20global%20arms%20market%20trends%E2%80%99%20that%20included%20%E2%80%98technology%20partnerships%E2%80%99%20which%20the%20corporation%20estimated%20would%20double%20to%2040%25%20by%202030.%20Responding%20to%20this%20declaration%2C%20a%20cross-section%20of%20security%20and%20industry%20officials%20in%20New%20Delhi%20interpreted%20it%20as%20an%20%E2%80%98admittance%E2%80%99%20by%20Russian%20defence%20companies%20of%20their%20inability%20to%20%E2%80%98effectively%E2%80%99%20continue%20delivering%20military%20equipment%20to%20their%20overseas%20clients%2C%20due%20to%C2%A0%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20urgent%20requirements%20to%20execute%20its%20Ukraine%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20India%20to%20persist%20in%20its%20dependence%20on%20Russia%20for%20its%20military%20equipment%20needs%20would%20not%20only%20be%20unrealistic%2C%20considering%20the%20sanctions-related%20constraints%2C%20but%20also%20operationally%20ruinous%2C%20given%20the%20battlefield%20setbacks%20Moscow%20has%20endured%20in%20Ukraine%20because%20of%20deploying.%20sub-standard%20materiel%E2%80%9D%20said%20analyst%20Brigadier%20Rahul%20Bhonsle%20of%20the%20Security%20Risks%20consultancy%20in%20Delhi.%20It%E2%80%99s%20time%2C%20he%20added%2C%20for%20India%20to%20jettison%20its%20dependency%20on%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20military%20industrial%20complex%20and%20look%20inwards%20and%20elsewhere%20overseas%20to%20fulfil%20these%20obligations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGeopolitics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20India%E2%80%99s%20senior-most%20soldier%2C%20Chief%20of%20Defence%20Staff%20General%20Anil%20Chauhan%20had%20declared%20recently%20that%20the%20geopolitical%20importance%20of%20Russia%20was%20declining%2C%20despite%20it%20being%20a%20nuclear%20weapons%20state.%C2%A0%20Delivering%20the%2014th%20Air%20Chief%20Marshal%20L.M.%20Katre%20memorial%20lecture%20in%20Bengaluru%20in%20early%20October%2C%20Gen%20Chauhan%20stated%20that%20the%20Wagner%20rebellion-referring%20to%20the%20stillborn%20mutiny%20by%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20state-funded%20rogue%20private%20army-indicated%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20internal%20weakness%20and%20reflected%20what%20adversity%20may%20lie%20in%20store%20for%20its%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeclining%20defence%20trade%20with%20Moscow%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20which%20a%20few%C2%A0examples%C2%A0indicate%2C%20only%20serves%20to%20further%20endorse%20the%20proliferating%20view%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20military%20and%20security%20circles%20of%20Russian%C2%A0unreliability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20(IAF)%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20%C2%A0had%20opted%20to%20bypass%20Moscow%20in%20upgrading%2084%20of%20its%20Sukhoi%20Su-30MKI%E2%80%99s%20to%20%E2%80%98Super%20Sukhoi%E2%80%99%20standards%2C%20in%20its%20first%20retrofit%20tranche%2C%20even%20though%20it%20had%20earlier%20been%20in%20talks%20with%20its%20Russian%20manufacturers%20for%20the%20platforms%20makeover.%20Also%2C%20the%20MoD%20had%20more%20or%20less%20decided%20to%20scrap%20the%20%241.2%20billion%202014%20tender%20for%20200%20Russian%20Kamov%20Ka-226T%20%E2%80%98Hoodlum%E2%80%99%20light%20utility%20helicopters%20for%20the%20IAF%20and%20the%20Army%20Aviation%20Corps%2C%20of%20which%2060%20were%20to%20be%20acquired%20in%20fly-away%20condition%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20series-built%20under%20a%20transfer%20of%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EArmy%20and%20Navy%20ditch%20Russian%20options%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20official%20sources%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20operational%2C%20availability%20and%C2%A0%20sustainability%20considerations%2C%20the%20IAF%20considered%20that%20even%20evaluating%20two%20fuel-intensive%20Russian%20fighters%20for%20its%20proposed%20acquisition%20of%20114%20multi-role%20fighter%20aircraft%20(MRFA)%2C%20was%20%E2%80%98irrational%20and%20unworkable%E2%80%99.%20They%20said%20the%20IAF%20continued%20to%20display%20lack%20of%20enthusiasm%20in%20even%20assessing%20United%20Aircraft%20Corporation%20and%20Sukhoi%20Corporation%E2%80%99s%20offer%20of%20MiG-35%20%E2%80%98Fulcrum-F%E2%80%99%20and%20Su-35%E2%80%99%20Flanker-E%E2%80%99%20for%20this%20tender%2C%20for%20which%20five%20other%20fighter%20makers%20had%20expressed%20interest%20in%20response%20to%20the%20forces%20April%202018%20Request%20for%20Information%20or%20RfI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IN%2C%20too%20had%20ditched%20the%20prospect%20of%20inducting%20Russian%20fighters%20into%20its%20new%20aircraft%20carrier%E2%80%99s%20combat%20air%20arm%2C%20to%20supplement%20the%2045%20twin-engine%20MiG29K%2FKUBs%20it%20had%20acquired%20between%202004%20and%202010%20for%20%242.29%20billion%2C%20and%20which%20had%20proven%20to%20be%20operationally%20inadequate.%20The%20service%20was%20presently%20in%20advanced%20negotiations%20to%20embark%2026%20French%20Rafale%20(Marine)%20fighters%20aboard%20INS%20Vikrant%20that%20was%20commissioned%20late%20last%20year.%20The%20IN%20is%20also%20believed%20to%20have%20halted%20negotiations%20with%20Russia%20to%20acquire%2010%20additional%20Kamov%20Ka-31%E2%80%99Helix%E2%80%99%20airborne%20early%20warning%20helicopters%20for%20%24520%20million%2C%20approved%20by%20the%20MoD%20in%20May%202019%2C%20for%20deployment%20aboard%20Vikrant%2C%20following%20uncertainty%20in%20supplies%20due%20to%20sanctions%20and%20attendant%20payment%20mechanisms%2C%20which%20endure%20and%20threaten%20to%20become%20even%20more%20acute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IA%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20that%20operates%203%2C500-odd%C2%A0%20licence-built%20Russian%20T72M1%20%E2%80%98Ajeya%E2%80%99%20main%20battle%20tank%20variants%20and%20directly%20imported%20and%20domestically%20assembled%20and%20constructed%20T90S%20%E2%80%98Bhishma%E2%80%99%20platforms%2C%20is%20almost%20certain%20not%20to%20acquire%20any%20more%20Russian%20tanks%20in%20future.%20Recent%20proposals%20to%20import%20Russian-origin%20Spurt-SDM1%20light%20amphibious%20tank%20were%20summarily%20abandoned%20in%20favour%20of%20Zorawar%2C%20the%20indigenously%20designed%20light%20tank%2C%20whose%20prototype%20was%20expected%20to%20begin%20trials%20early%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHomegrown%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20domestic%20alternative%20is%20also%20imminent%20to%20supplement%20and%20eventually%20replace%20around%20800-odd%20of%20the%20IA%E2%80%99s%20licence%20built%20Soviet-era%20Boyevaya%20Mashina%20Pyekhoty%20(BMP)2%2F2K%20%E2%80%98Sarath%E2%80%99%20infantry%20combat%20vehicles%20(ICVs)%20via%20the%20local%2C%20but%20long%20deferred%20Future%20Combat%20Vehicle%20(FRCV)%20programme.%20This%20envisages%20the%20development%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98family%E2%80%99%20of%20tracked%20armoured%20vehicles%20which%20other%20than%20MBTs%2C%20would%20include%20ICVs%20and%20tank%20recovery%20and%20bridge-laying%20variants.%20However%2C%20the%20blighted%20Ak-203%20rifles%20would%2C%20once%20they%20emerge%2C%20remain%20the%20IA%E2%80%99s%20sole%20contemporary%20Russian%20hardware%20induction%20in%20multiple%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsidering%20the%20aforementioned%C2%A0actualities%2C%C2%A0it%E2%80%99s%20obvious%20that%20the%20sun%20is%20setting%20swiftly%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20continued%C2%A0reliance%C2%A0on%20Russian%20defence%20equipment%2C%20even%20though%20Moscow%20will%2C%20no%20doubt%2C%20take%20commercial%20solace%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20some%2060%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20overall%20in-service%20military%20platforms%20were%20of%20Russian%20and%20Soviet-era%20origin%2C%20and%20in%20need%20of%20support%20and%20sustenance%20for%20several%20more%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20the%20impending%20end%20of%20an%20epoch%20beginning%20the%20early%201960s%2C%20in%20which%20India%20steadily%20built%20its%20arsenal%20with%20Russian%20assistance%2C%20for%20an%20estimated%20%2470%20billion%20is%20never%20easy%3B%20but%20it%20remains%20necessary%20for%20future%20security%20in%20a%20turbulent%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703856183000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F29184807%2FGCW4z6zWEAAr0qe.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fjaishankar-russia-materiel-defence%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20was%20no%20indication%20that%20the%20two%20sides%20had%20resolved%20the%20knotty%20problem%20of%20India%20paying%20Russia%20for%20military%20gear%2C%20which%20has%20been%20bedevilling%20both%20sides%20for%2012-14%20months%2C%20after%20US-led%20sanctions%20were%20imposed%20on%20Russia%20for%20invading%20Ukraine.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fjaishankar-russia-materiel-defence%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shipping%20costs%20reach%2015%20month%20high%20despite%20some%20restoration%20of%20Red%20Sea%20route%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703855940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-container-shipping_6406760.jpg%3F20231229132832%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ffreight-price-up-80-despite-return-of-some-red-sea-journeys-13039090%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20cost%20of%20shipping%20goods%20has%20again%20grown%20significantly%20as%20freight%20giants%20continue%20to%20avoid%20the%20key%20Red%20Sea%20route%20and%20unions%20expand%20protections%20for%20mariners.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ffreight-price-up-80-despite-return-of-some-red-sea-journeys-13039090%22%2C%22cd